3 EASY drills to perfect your KB clean ✨
_
Kettlebell work can be daunting in the beginning. Bruised forearms lead to bruised egos quick! We talked about the KB swing before so let's progress to some fun stuff!
---
❗️Things to conquer before the clean❗️
- bilateral swing: made a quick video on that and I'll post on my stories for that reminder.
--
THE DRILLS!
- SINGLE ARM SWING: very same set up as the bilateral swing. The grip is going to be on the furthest corner of the horn for the working arm. Make sure your free hand is supporting the movement by matching it with the working/loaded arm. 
- LOW PISTOL ROW: great way to start playing with the control of the momentum. Make sure your wrist stays nice and neutral so when you pull back you aren't allowing the bell to flip. Work on timing here. This is the difference between really bruised forearms and kinda bruised forearms. (Forearms will inevitably take a beating when building your quality of KB work)
- PUNCH THROUGH: Now this is where the pistol row has lead us. There is a sweat spot for the punch through and it changes depending on how high/close you want to receive your clean. Even the weight of the KB can change that sweat spot. This is a drill that you really just need to do often to figure that out. Good luck and have fun!
--
Once you start to unlock some of these movements you can start to really progress your training!
-
Check me out on the @technogym training app for workouts and all things fitness! 
___________________________________________

We all have heard of the 75 HARD challenge.... this is a bit more accessible.
___________
I'm starting this for the average person to get some momentum under their belt. We are looking for adaptations that are a bit more sustainable. Referring to it as the "soft" version doesn't make this easy btw. Here are the rules.
____
1: 🏋🏽‍♀️Workout daily. 1 day a week should be a rest day. Strive to strength train 3x a week, condition 2x a week and work on mobility 1x a week. Train with me (link in bio) and I can help with that.
2: 💦Drink 3 liter liters of water daily.
3: Read 10+ pages of an actual book. No audio books.
4: 🚶‍♂️Walk 7,500k+ steps daily.
5: 🥗Prioritize Whole Foods. Aka cut out BS. I'm personally going to be a little lax on this only because I'll be traveling a ton, but a good 85/15 split between Whole Foods and naughty things seems like a good goal to me. 
6: 🍷NO HARD LIQUOR. (Wine ok but sparingly)
7: NO 🍃🍃... not a great mental health contributor.
***BONUS***
Focus on better habits. Making your bed in the morning. Journal daily. Meditate. Spend time outdoors. Connect with others. Basically we want to help facilitate your overall. Which is to prioritize our overall health and wellness. 
___
You won't be doing this alone. I'll be posting daily to keep myself honest. I would love to see your efforts too. Tag me in your stories/post and I'll make sure to swing by with some energy hyping you up. September 5th is 75 days from now... YOU READY?
_________
#75hard #75softchallenge

Swipe right for your next workout 😘
___
@meghan_hayden_ and I came up with a fun flow and then broke it down to a simple EMOM.

THE WORK:
20 min EMOM: 30s on 30s off
1: Russian swing: high hike/thumb to bum action 🤗
2: Clean to transverse lunge: encouraged to go barefoot or training shoes.. no running shoes or a rolled ankle is in your near future.
3: Push press w/ negative release: anchor your ribs down to prevent dumping in your back. Elbows 45degrees in.
4: Bent arm press: any tension in the front of the shoulder is a sign you are doing it wrong. Posterior delt or bust.
5: Alt snatches: release the beast!

⚠️ these moves are technical and should be done with intention. If you have never performed these moves please work with a kettlebell specialist before completing. 
_____
Stay tuned for how we put them together for a fun flow.

BEGINNER KB FLOW

Grab your flow partner and get to work 

✈️ SWING
✈️ CLEAN TO 2 REVERSE LUNGE
✈️ BENT OVER ROW
✈️ HALO

KB flows offer an opportunity to work on coordination, master your skills, and challenge your conditioning. 

Once you’ve nailed down the movements individually, combine them in a flow to test your proficiency.

Integration:
Warm up: pick a light weight and open up the body by warming up the movements you plan to focus on in your lift 
Finisher: Challenge your coordination and brain power when pre-fatigued. 
As an EMOM or Tabata: tight on time? Complete this flow with a :30-:45 rest between for 5-10 rounds 

However you choose to apply this flow, move intentionally, have fun, and challenge your partner to elevate

Birthday vibes 🎂
__
Today is officially my bday and to celebrate my 35 years on this earth here are 35 things I've learned.
--
1: Develop what you are naturally good at.
2: Start eating fermented foods. Now.
3: Real friends tell you hard truths.
4: Failures are your best teachers.
5: Korean skin care hits different.
6: Therapy. Get into it.
7: It's never too late to start investing.
8: Move your body because you can.
9: Learn to banter with strangers.
10: Travel often and experience different foods/cultures/languages
11: Love in every possible way. Friendships/animals/husbands/wives/work relationships... they all matter.
12: Read more.
15: Floss dammit.
16: Learn something new every year.
17: Strength train 3x a week.
18: If you are in a position to help others do it to its full extent.
19: If chasing coin is how you make decisions you will never be content.
20: DANCE EVERY DAY
21: Do good human shit.
22: Don't stress over anything you can't change in 3 mins.
23: Your relationship with yourself will dictate how you allow others to treat you.
24: Learn to cook 1 dish really well. It's sexy.
25: Always remember that if you are IN the room, you deserve to be IN that room.
26: Deal with the hard emotions when they come up. Don't run away from yourself or others.
27: Eat your deep leafy greens and colorful produce.
28: If you say you're going to do something DO IT.
29: Listen more.
30: Your parents did what they could with what they had. They are human too.
31: Learn to share your feelings with those around you. Let ppl in. 
32: Add a lil salt to your Water.
33: Drugs are silly.
34: Ask for help. Give ppl an opportunity to show up for you.
35: We made up this whole thing. All the rules and competitions. We are on a big rock floating in space. Lighten up 😘

Title: Objectify
Artist: @suzykellemsdominik 
__
I met Suzy on a trip in #oaxaca and a few months later she asked me to get naked for her....😆
--
Working with her was super collaborative. She came to me with this idea and I completely understood her vision and instantly wanted to be apart of it. I love the imagery and sculptures we did together and I'm excited that it's finally coming to light.
__
Check out some of the behind the scenes work on my stories and where to find the rest of the work on her IG @suzykellemsdominik 
_
#art #photographylovers #sculpture #femalegaze

Project: Objectify 2022
_
When I was asked to be apart of this project I was both nervous and excited. For a brief (very brief) moment I was signed with Wilhelmina Models back in day. My favorite thing about that period was working with photographers and artist. (I will always be a creative at heart) So when @suzykellemsdominik told me about her vision and what she wanted to capture... I was so game!
-
This is her perspective on "objectifying" the male body through the female gaze. I think her POV really gave these images a sense of serenity that wouldn't have been present without her. It's so easy to show nudity for the sake of nudity and even though the purpose was to "objectify" me I don't think the work captured a defeated or even helpless man. I think there is some inherent safety under the female gaze. I think that's what we captured.
--
#artwork #modelshoot #jacksonhole

5 things you need to know about changing your body composition.
__
1: Cardio does not kill gains. Adding 20-30 mins post training session of either walking or light jogging is great for recovery and a bonus calorie expenditure. 
2: Stop demonizing certain macros. In a strength training program carbs are essential, fats are needed for hormonal regulation and protein is .7- 1x your body weight in lbs. Maybe up to 1.2x if you are on a cut.
3: You're eating too late and sleeping like shit. Sleep is the GOAT when it comes to developing muscle. Focus on solid sleep practices. I'm a big fan of l-theanine and gaba before bed.
4: You aren't lifting heavy enough. On a scale between 1-10 (10 being the hardest) you want to be lifting at least at a 7 on your training days. 
5: It's not easy but it's not complicated. There is a ton of misinformation and a lot of general information out there on how to change your body and promises of quick fixes, but once you understand the basics you can filter out the BS. Eat whole foods, the rainbow and organic when appropriate. Train often, varied in intensities and with good form.
